<H3>Operations</H3>
<P>

<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=2 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=650>
        <TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=100% NOWRAP COLSPAN=2>
        <I><NOBR>
    <TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP NOWRAP><I>
    <A HREF="Class_Random_points_on_segment_2.html#Cross_link_anchor_1704">Random_points_on_segment_2</A>&lt;<A HREF="../Kernel_23_ref/Class_Point_2.html#Cross_link_anchor_52">Point_2</A>, Creator&gt; g ( </I></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP NOWRAP><I>
     <A HREF="../Kernel_23_ref/Class_Point_2.html#Cross_link_anchor_52">Point_2</A> p,<BR>

<A HREF="../Kernel_23_ref/Class_Point_2.html#Cross_link_anchor_52">Point_2</A> q,<BR>

Random&amp; rnd = default_random);</I></TD></TR></TABLE>
    
        </I></NOBR>
        </TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH=30% NOWRAP></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=70%>
    <MATH><I>g</I></MATH> is an input iterator creating points of type <I><A HREF="../Kernel_23_ref/Class_Point_2.html#Cross_link_anchor_52">Point_2</A></I> uniformly
  distributed on the segment from <MATH><I>p</I></MATH> to <MATH><I>q</I></MATH> (excluding <MATH><I>q</I></MATH>),
  i.e.&nbsp;<MATH><I><I>*g</I> == (1-<IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=7 HEIGHT=13 ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="cc_lambda.gif">) p + <IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=7 HEIGHT=13 ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="cc_lambda.gif">q</I></MATH> where <MATH><I>0  <IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=11 HEIGHT=25 ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="cc_leq.gif"> <IMG BORDER=0 WIDTH=7 HEIGHT=13 ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="cc_lambda.gif">&lt; 1</I></MATH>&nbsp;.
  A single random number is needed from <I>rnd</I> for each point.<BR>

<EM>Requirement: </EM>The expressions <I>to_double(p.x())</I> and
    <I>to_double(p.y())</I> must  result in the respective
    <I>double</I> representation of the coordinates of <MATH><I>p</I></MATH>,
    and similarly for <MATH><I>q</I></MATH>.
<P>

</TD></TR>
        </TABLE>
<P>

